cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "cobalt-sentinel: SS-CBD Sequential Semantic Cosine Behavioral Distance"
abstract: >
  Implementation of SS-CBD (Sequential Semantic Cosine Behavioral Distance),
  a method for detecting identity drift in autonomous AI agents by combining
  Wald's SPRT, semantic action embeddings, and tier-weighted operational risk.
  Includes 7 baselines (LRT, Chi², JS, Hellinger, CBD, ADWIN, CUSUM) and
  complete experimental infrastructure for reproducible evaluation.
authors:
